WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:11.378
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:32.432 --> 00:35.068
- Okay, class,
now that we're done crafting,

00:35.135 --> 00:36.936
it's time to name our puppets.

00:37.003 --> 00:40.039
{\an3}I named mine
Miss Genevieve Perriwinkle.

00:40.106 --> 00:42.208
She's a saucy bayou chef.

00:42.275 --> 00:44.344
{\an1}[in Cajun accent]
<i>Enchanté,</i> children.

00:44.411 --> 00:47.547
- My puppet's name is Bethany.

00:47.614 --> 00:49.649
Bethany is very sick.

00:49.716 --> 00:52.185
{\an3}- That's okay
because my puppet is a doctor.

00:52.252 --> 00:54.220
I think I'm gonna name him...

00:54.287 --> 00:56.356
{\an3}Brad.
Brad Paxton.

00:56.423 --> 00:59.025
{\an3}[robust voice]
H'yuck, hi, there, buddy.

00:59.092 --> 01:00.960
[normal voice]
No, too weird.

01:01.027 --> 01:02.328
[in British accent]
Good day, old chap.

01:02.395 --> 01:04.197
{\an3}[normal voice]
No, no, that's not it.

01:04.263 --> 01:05.732
The voice will come to me.

01:05.799 --> 01:07.634
all: [chanting]
Fight!

01:07.700 --> 01:08.902
[crashing]
- Huh?

01:08.968 --> 01:10.170
What's going on out there?

01:10.236 --> 01:12.138
- You take it back, Dade.
- Or else!

01:12.205 --> 01:14.474
{\an1}- Oh, yeah?
Bring it.

01:14.541 --> 01:15.708
[both grunt]

01:15.775 --> 01:17.043
- [gasps]
[all grunting]

01:17.110 --> 01:19.579
[in Cajun accent]
Good heavens.

01:19.646 --> 01:22.582
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:22.649 --> 01:29.389
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:29.456 --> 01:32.459
- You shut your filthy mouth!
You shut it!

01:32.525 --> 01:35.728
{\an1}- Ugh, your breath is so bad
it's making my eyes water.

01:35.795 --> 01:38.264
{\an3}- Ah!
I'm shouting too!

01:38.331 --> 01:40.066
{\an1}- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:40.133 --> 01:42.068
What's the problem?
- [grunting]

01:42.135 --> 01:43.670
{\an3}Oh, thank goodness you're here,
Harvey.

01:43.736 --> 01:46.639
{\an3}Maybe you can talk some sense
into these lunatics.

01:46.706 --> 01:49.409
- Dade thinks strawberry
flavored Toastie Tarts

01:49.476 --> 01:51.978
are better than s'mores flavored
Toastie Tarts.

01:52.045 --> 01:53.313
- Blasphemy.

01:53.379 --> 01:55.982
- S'mores are not
a breakfast food.

01:56.049 --> 01:58.251
They're just not!
- Now, guys,

01:58.318 --> 02:00.420
{\an1}how about we focus on
some common ground?

02:00.487 --> 02:03.890
{\an3}- There's no wrong time of day
for s'mores, you monster.

02:03.957 --> 02:07.694
{\an3}- Ugh, I'm not gonna listen to
someone who wears a potato sack.

02:07.760 --> 02:08.961
[grunts]

02:09.027 --> 02:11.431
- You smell like old ham.

02:11.498 --> 02:13.333
[all grunting]

02:14.200 --> 02:17.237
- I got 'em.

02:17.303 --> 02:19.772
You kids need to calm down.

02:19.839 --> 02:21.441
{\an3}But off the record,
I gotta say,

02:21.508 --> 02:24.544
{\an3}I'm impressed
with your fighting skills.

02:24.611 --> 02:26.713
- That was quite a tiff.

02:26.779 --> 02:29.849
Well, I guess you gotta agree
to disagree.

02:29.916 --> 02:31.451
- Oh, we agree on one thing.

02:31.518 --> 02:34.454
{\an3}- I never wanna
see those two again.

02:34.521 --> 02:36.256
- Are you guys being serious?

02:36.322 --> 02:39.292
- I have been nothing but civil,
and what do I get?

02:39.359 --> 02:41.227
Rashes.
I get rashes.

02:41.294 --> 02:44.998
- I put up with him 'cause
I thought he'd die eventually,

02:45.064 --> 02:47.233
but when he speaks,
my hair falls out.

02:47.300 --> 02:49.168
- I don't enjoy him.

02:49.235 --> 02:51.838
- Yeah, okay, but can't we--

02:51.905 --> 02:53.540
- Enough of this.
Come on, Harvey.

02:53.606 --> 02:55.742
Let's get out of here.
- Yeah, right, meat-brain.

02:55.808 --> 02:57.076
Harvey's coming we us.

02:57.143 --> 02:58.711
{\an3}- Oh, like fun
he's coming with you.

02:58.778 --> 03:01.314
He's coming with me.
- No, he's coming with me.

03:01.381 --> 03:03.583
{\an3}- Harvey, go on.
Tell 'em I'm your best friend.

03:03.650 --> 03:05.485
{\an3}- Dude, you know
we're your best friend.

03:05.552 --> 03:06.986
- Come on, Harvey, let's go.
- Get this over with.

03:07.053 --> 03:08.454
Ditch this guy.
- Harvey.

03:08.521 --> 03:10.757
- Harvey.
- Come home.

03:10.823 --> 03:12.525
- Dade is friend.

03:12.592 --> 03:14.894
Fee, Foo, friend.

03:14.961 --> 03:16.329
I...I...

03:16.396 --> 03:19.365
I choose both!
both: What?

03:19.432 --> 03:21.301
- If you guys don't want
to see each other,

03:21.367 --> 03:23.703
then I'll just hang out
with you both separately.

03:23.770 --> 03:27.640
That way everyone will be happy.
So, what do you say?

03:27.707 --> 03:29.108
- [growls]

03:29.175 --> 03:31.110
- All right, deal.

03:31.177 --> 03:32.979
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

03:33.046 --> 03:34.881
- And some rustic Dijon.

03:34.948 --> 03:37.884
Voilà.
The perfect sandwich.

03:37.951 --> 03:39.185
There's nothing better

03:39.252 --> 03:40.587
than sharing a meal
with your friends.

03:40.653 --> 03:44.257
- I can unhinge my jaw.
Ah...

03:44.324 --> 03:46.726
- Let's dig in.

03:46.793 --> 03:48.127
{\an3}[sighs]

03:48.194 --> 03:50.730
[horn blows]
Oh, that's the Harvey Horn.

03:50.797 --> 03:52.165
Dade must be calling.

03:52.231 --> 03:54.500
{\an1}- Ugh, that guy.
I'll admit.

03:54.567 --> 03:56.135
{\an1}I wasn't sure
about this arrangement,

03:56.202 --> 03:57.670
but its pretty great now that

03:57.737 --> 03:59.372
{\an1}I don't have to see
his face anymore.

03:59.439 --> 04:01.941
{\an3}- It's different,
but it works for us.

04:02.008 --> 04:03.876
- [chuckles weakly]
Yeah.

04:03.943 --> 04:05.411
I'll see you guys later.

04:05.478 --> 04:08.615
[horn blowing]
[panting]

04:10.883 --> 04:12.251
{\an1}Hey, Dade.
I heard the horn.

04:12.318 --> 04:14.087
What's up?
- I hope you came hungry

04:14.153 --> 04:16.623
'cause I made sandwiches.

04:16.689 --> 04:18.291
- Uh...

04:18.358 --> 04:20.093
{\an3}- Go ahead.
Dig in.

04:20.159 --> 04:22.462
- Uh, I actually already ate.

04:22.528 --> 04:24.597
- What?
- But I can eat more.

04:24.664 --> 04:26.099
a lot more.

04:26.165 --> 04:28.368
[breathing heavily]

04:28.434 --> 04:29.535
[groans]

04:31.704 --> 04:34.941
Oh, it's Fee and Foo's
Harvey Drum.

04:35.008 --> 04:36.342
- Oh, those two.

04:36.409 --> 04:38.645
{\an3}Just don't let 'em
give you lice again.

04:38.711 --> 04:40.747
[panting]

04:40.813 --> 04:43.216
{\an1}- Come on, Harvey.
We gotta climb higher.

04:43.282 --> 04:45.051
{\an3}- Coming.

04:45.118 --> 04:46.152
- [sniffing]

04:46.219 --> 04:48.521
{\an1}I think you tracked back
his scent.

04:48.588 --> 04:50.189
- Oh, sorry.

04:50.256 --> 04:51.791
<i>[quirky music]</i>

04:51.858 --> 04:53.292
{\an1}- There.
Much better.

04:53.359 --> 04:54.761
[horn blows]

04:54.827 --> 04:57.230
- Oh.
Whoa!

04:57.296 --> 04:59.699
- You're looking
very regal there, buddy.

04:59.766 --> 05:00.900
{\an1}- Oh.

05:00.967 --> 05:02.635
{\an3}- With those two cretins
out of my life,

05:02.702 --> 05:04.437
I've stopped grinding my teeth.

05:04.504 --> 05:07.306
- [groans]
When I move, there's pain.

05:07.373 --> 05:08.641
[drum beating]

05:08.708 --> 05:09.742
[groans]

05:09.809 --> 05:12.145
[both laughing]

05:12.211 --> 05:13.613
[horn blows]

05:13.680 --> 05:15.615
[drum beating]

05:15.682 --> 05:17.016
[horn blows]

05:17.083 --> 05:20.219
[drum beating, horn blowing]

05:26.626 --> 05:29.762
Well, everyone had
a great time today.

05:29.829 --> 05:32.632
Just gotta keep this up
for the rest of my life.

05:32.699 --> 05:34.100
[coughs]

05:34.167 --> 05:35.835
Ah, there's a tooth.

05:35.902 --> 05:37.170
- Hey, over here.

05:37.236 --> 05:40.206
Look, I do not wanna be
near these two weirdos.

05:40.273 --> 05:42.709
{\an1}- Oh, sorry.
I'll move you.

05:42.775 --> 05:45.578
- Thanks, buddy.
- Hey, what about us?

05:45.645 --> 05:47.780
We don't want
to be reminded every day

05:47.847 --> 05:50.216
of Dade's
wild west themed birthday.

05:50.283 --> 05:52.819
- Oh, shut up.
You guys are just jealous.

05:52.885 --> 05:54.587
- Okay, let me--

05:54.654 --> 05:56.589
- I don't want
our frames to touch.

05:56.656 --> 05:58.057
- Yeah, I can agree with that.

05:58.124 --> 06:00.059
- Ugh, fix it, Harvey.

06:00.126 --> 06:01.661
- Get me outta here.

06:01.728 --> 06:03.062
- I'd prefer the other side.
- Separate us.

06:03.129 --> 06:04.430
- Don't make me deal with him.

06:04.497 --> 06:06.332
both: I hate that guy.
- I hate their presence.

06:06.399 --> 06:08.434
{\an1}- Hey, I don't wanna be
stuck here with him.

06:08.501 --> 06:10.403
- Harvey, rip this photo up.

06:10.470 --> 06:12.138
- Rip it up.
- Break it.

06:12.205 --> 06:14.474
- But that was
ultimate Frisbee day.

06:14.540 --> 06:16.309
I love that memory.

06:16.375 --> 06:17.877
[glass shatters]
No!

06:17.944 --> 06:19.412
[screams]

06:19.479 --> 06:20.847
This isn't working.

06:20.913 --> 06:23.950
How can I teach these guys
about friendship?

06:25.051 --> 06:26.986
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

06:27.053 --> 06:28.855
Ooh.

06:28.921 --> 06:31.557
Thank you all for putting aside
your grievances

06:31.624 --> 06:33.593
and joining me here.
- For the record,

06:33.659 --> 06:36.829
I did not know
these two would be here.

06:36.896 --> 06:39.766
{\an3}- If I knew he was coming,
I would have brought a Taser.

06:39.832 --> 06:41.734
{\an3}- I've put together
a presentation

06:41.801 --> 06:45.271
{\an3}and it's called How to Be Nice
Even If You Disagree.

06:45.338 --> 06:46.572
{\an1}- Just so you know.
I'm only here

06:46.639 --> 06:48.808
to support my best friend.

06:48.875 --> 06:50.209
- Go to sleep, Dade.

06:50.276 --> 06:53.412
- I hope you
find this educational.

06:53.479 --> 06:54.747
<i>[fanfare music playing</i>
<i>over stereo]</i>

06:54.814 --> 06:57.316
Hi, everyone.
I'm Harvey.

06:57.383 --> 06:59.085
[nasally voice]
And I'm Brad Paxton.

06:59.152 --> 07:01.654
[normal voice] Hey, Brad,
what's your favorite color?

07:01.721 --> 07:03.422
[nasally voice] Red.
[normal voice] That's cool.

07:03.489 --> 07:05.091
My favorite color's blue.

07:05.158 --> 07:06.526
[nasally voice]
Well, I disagree,

07:06.592 --> 07:08.694
and I think your sweater's
real ugly.

07:08.761 --> 07:11.063
[normal voice] Now, Brad,
that wasn't very nice.

07:11.130 --> 07:12.298
{\an1}- Hey!

07:12.365 --> 07:14.133
{\an3}You can't talk to Harvey
like that.

07:14.200 --> 07:16.302
- His sweater is not ugly.

07:16.369 --> 07:19.338
- Um, the audience participation
part of the show

07:19.405 --> 07:20.506
is coming soon.

07:20.573 --> 07:22.809
Brad, just because we disagree,

07:22.875 --> 07:24.777
doesn't mean we should be mean
to each other.

07:24.844 --> 07:27.613
[nasally voice] Oh, yeah?
Well, I think you're a goober.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.615
Whoa!
- Harvey's not a goober!

07:29.682 --> 07:31.250
He's a sweet boy!

07:31.317 --> 07:32.518
- Boo! Boo!
- Leave Harvey alone,

07:32.585 --> 07:33.553
you big jerk!
- I'm furious!

07:33.619 --> 07:35.588
- Guys, if you keep shouting

07:35.655 --> 07:37.323
then I can't finish the show.

07:37.390 --> 07:39.992
{\an1}- [gasps]
He's got Harvey's arm.

07:40.059 --> 07:42.395
- But this is a puppet.

07:42.461 --> 07:44.530
- Destroy him!
- [screams]

07:44.597 --> 07:46.933
{\an3}You guys are missing
the point of the lesson!

07:46.999 --> 07:48.334
both: Ah!
- Blood!

07:48.401 --> 07:51.604
- I've finally fixed
my steam balloon.

07:51.671 --> 07:54.674
Just in time for my steamy date.

07:54.740 --> 07:57.777
[laughs]
Things are looking up for Moff.

07:57.844 --> 08:00.813
[leave rustle]
Ah, I gotta hide.

08:00.880 --> 08:03.649
<i>[exciting music]</i>

08:03.716 --> 08:04.750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:04.817 --> 08:06.219
- [panting]
Where'd he go?

08:06.285 --> 08:09.822
Oh, wh--what if he makes fun
of Harvey's giant head?

08:09.889 --> 08:12.158
- But that's Harvey's
biggest insecurity.

08:12.225 --> 08:13.693
- That's why he avoids hats.

08:13.759 --> 08:15.862
- I'm gonna get you,
Brad Paxton!

08:15.928 --> 08:18.898
{\an1}- Hey, they aren't
arguing anymore.

08:18.965 --> 08:21.567
It's like they're too busy
being mad at you.

08:21.634 --> 08:22.869
[nasally voice]
They're hatred

08:22.935 --> 08:25.671
for a common enemy
is uniting them, Harvey.

08:25.738 --> 08:27.039
[normal voice]
You're right.

08:27.106 --> 08:28.941
Brad, I'm sorry.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.610
You've been
a good puppet friend,

08:30.676 --> 08:33.613
but now could you be
a puppet villain?

08:33.679 --> 08:36.482
[nasally voice]
I'm whatever you need me to be.

08:36.549 --> 08:39.684
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:39.751 --> 08:41.520
Guys, I'm up here!

08:41.587 --> 08:43.322
[nasally voice]
[laughs evilly]

08:43.389 --> 08:44.757
That's right!

08:44.824 --> 08:47.026
I'm holding Harvey hostage...
all: Oh, no!

08:47.093 --> 08:49.195
- [nasally voice]
And I'll never let him go

08:49.262 --> 08:51.697
because he's a huge doody head.

08:51.764 --> 08:55.034
- Brad, you stop it.
- Just wait till I get up there.

08:55.101 --> 08:57.904
- [nasally voice] The only way
you could possibly rescue Harvey

08:57.970 --> 09:00.172
is if you
put aside your differences

09:00.239 --> 09:02.074
and work together.
- What?

09:02.141 --> 09:05.344
{\an3}No, I'm not working
with these two bozos.

09:05.411 --> 09:06.646
- Yeah, ew.

09:06.712 --> 09:08.281
We'll just
save Harvey ourselves.

09:08.347 --> 09:10.716
- No, I'm saving Harvey.

09:10.783 --> 09:12.285
I got the rope first.
- Let go, Dade.

09:12.351 --> 09:14.553
We're gonna save Harvey.
You're not needed here.

09:14.620 --> 09:15.922
{\an1}- You get your dirty hands
off me.

09:15.988 --> 09:19.158
{\an3}- Oh, uh...
maybe more cooperatively?

09:19.225 --> 09:23.062
- Stop trying to spread
your garbage everywhere.

09:23.129 --> 09:26.132
Oh, no.
- What?

09:26.198 --> 09:28.734
- Emily, we met at Applebark's.

09:28.801 --> 09:31.470
You said to only call
when my blimp was ready.

09:31.537 --> 09:34.340
Well, guess what?
I...

09:34.407 --> 09:37.376
never mind.

09:37.443 --> 09:38.978
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:39.045 --> 09:41.814
- Don't worry, Harvey.
- This is all your fault!

09:41.881 --> 09:43.883
[both grunting]

09:43.950 --> 09:46.986
- Oh, no!
Tornadobark!

09:47.053 --> 09:48.054
- Harvey!

09:48.120 --> 09:51.057
- [screaming]

09:51.123 --> 09:52.725
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:52.792 --> 09:55.194
- We'll never save him
if we keep fighting each other.

09:55.261 --> 09:56.796
{\an1}- [growls]

09:56.862 --> 09:58.597
{\an3}- [growls]

09:58.664 --> 10:00.633
{\an1}- Fine.
Let's save our friend.

10:00.700 --> 10:02.902
{\an3}- Fine.
I think we should come up with

10:02.969 --> 10:06.339
a careful, rational,
and safe plan that--

10:06.405 --> 10:08.207
this is not what I was saying!

10:08.274 --> 10:09.875
[screams]

10:09.942 --> 10:11.978
- [screaming]

10:12.044 --> 10:13.279
Huh?

10:13.346 --> 10:16.048
[all screaming]
Guys!

10:16.115 --> 10:19.652
You guys did it.
You worked together.

10:19.719 --> 10:20.920
[thumping]
- Take that and that!

10:20.987 --> 10:22.254
- I'm gonna mess you up.
- And that!

10:22.321 --> 10:24.223
- I'm gonna punch your eyeballs!

10:24.290 --> 10:31.163
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:32.798 --> 10:35.735
- We're okay!
You saved me!

10:35.801 --> 10:39.005
So you guys put aside your
differences and made up, right?

10:39.071 --> 10:40.606
- No, no,.
- We still hate him.

10:40.673 --> 10:42.141
{\an3}- Yeah, "hate" is
the word I would use,

10:42.208 --> 10:44.477
{\an3}but we can't be sure
if that Brad character

10:44.543 --> 10:46.245
is gone for good.

10:46.312 --> 10:47.680
- He could still be out there.

10:47.747 --> 10:51.617
{\an1}- Until we know Harvey is safe
from all danger, truce?

10:51.684 --> 10:53.352
{\an3}- [sighs]
Truce.

10:53.419 --> 10:55.788
- Yeah, we're all friends again.

10:55.855 --> 10:58.524
- Now how do we get down?

10:58.591 --> 11:00.026
[screams, grunts]

11:00.092 --> 11:02.228
Dang it, Fee.

11:02.294 --> 11:03.496
[wheezing]

11:03.562 --> 11:05.564
- Oh, my, a balloon accident.

11:05.631 --> 11:07.433
Oh, a puppet friend.

11:07.500 --> 11:08.701
[in Cajun accent]
<i>Enchanté.</i>

11:08.768 --> 11:10.202
What's your name, sugar?

11:10.269 --> 11:12.104
[in British accent]
Oh, good day, madam.

11:12.171 --> 11:14.740
- No, that's not the voice.
Eh, it'll come to me.

11:16.642 --> 11:18.577
all: Yeah!

11:18.644 --> 11:21.447
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

11:21.514 --> 11:23.849
[all giggling]

11:23.916 --> 11:26.252
- A little to the left.

11:26.318 --> 11:29.055
[both laughing]

11:29.121 --> 11:30.823
- It's so nice of you
to bring out

11:30.890 --> 11:32.525
{\an1}your little siblings
to lunch, Dade.

11:32.591 --> 11:34.326
- [wheezing]

11:34.393 --> 11:36.529
- Oh.
- Nope.

11:36.595 --> 11:38.330
Over here, Harvey.
- Oh.

11:38.397 --> 11:39.498
- You gotta keep
the rowdier ones

11:39.565 --> 11:41.467
{\an3}on a short leash.
Stay.

11:41.534 --> 11:43.836
- [hisses]
- Oh, sorry, Dade.

11:43.903 --> 11:46.238
{\an1}You and your siblings
all kind of look the same.

11:46.305 --> 11:49.375
{\an3}- Oh, that's okay, Harvey.
Easy mistake.

11:49.442 --> 11:52.344
But it stings just the same.

11:52.411 --> 11:54.780
- [screaming]

11:54.847 --> 11:57.983
<i>[quirky lilting music]</i>

11:58.050 --> 12:04.790
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:04.857 --> 12:06.926
[all clamoring]
- [grunting]

12:06.992 --> 12:08.494
Let me in.

12:08.561 --> 12:10.896
Hello, I exist too.

12:10.963 --> 12:14.600
- Sorry, little boy.
What would you like?

12:14.667 --> 12:15.968
- To be an only child.

12:16.035 --> 12:17.903
- We're out of chili.

12:17.970 --> 12:20.039
- Ugh, I'll have
a cheese sandwich.

12:20.106 --> 12:22.875
- A cheese sandwich.
- Wait, I'm not done.

12:22.942 --> 12:25.678
Uh, with mayonnaise,
but only on one side.

12:25.744 --> 12:27.513
{\an1}Oh, oh, and, uh, back
to the cheese,.

12:27.580 --> 12:28.948
Make sure it's Swiss,

12:29.014 --> 12:31.517
and I-I want a pickle on a spear

12:31.584 --> 12:33.252
through the middle on top.

12:33.319 --> 12:36.021
- What a special order.

12:36.088 --> 12:38.124
- Oh... [chuckles]
Why, thank you.

12:38.190 --> 12:41.026
- I think I'll add that
to the menu.

12:41.093 --> 12:43.462
What's your name, little boy?

12:43.529 --> 12:44.897
- Uh, Dade.

12:44.964 --> 12:49.135
- Well, Dade,
you're the new special.

12:49.201 --> 12:52.471
- [gasps]
I'm special.

12:52.538 --> 12:53.839
[bell dings]
- Order up.

12:53.906 --> 12:55.508
all: Ooh.
- [giggles]

12:55.574 --> 12:58.010
All right, make way.
Special boy coming through.

12:58.077 --> 12:59.945
Important announcement,
everyone.

13:00.012 --> 13:01.614
Have you heard about
the hottest new hoagie

13:01.680 --> 13:03.082
on the menu?
- No.

13:03.149 --> 13:05.050
- It's called The Dade.
Check it out.

13:05.117 --> 13:06.986
It's right up there
on the special's board.

13:07.052 --> 13:09.388
{\an1}- But I thought
only famous people

13:09.455 --> 13:10.890
got stuff named after them.

13:10.956 --> 13:12.558
I don't know who you are.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.426
- Well, now you won't forget.

13:14.493 --> 13:17.563
- What'll you have?
- Uh, I'll have--

13:17.630 --> 13:19.331
{\an3}- No, no, no,
I got this, Claire.

13:19.398 --> 13:21.867
She'll have The Dade.

13:21.934 --> 13:24.603
{\an3}- But I'm very allergic
to bread.

13:24.670 --> 13:28.307
{\an3}- Make that
a protein-style Dade.

13:28.374 --> 13:31.310
{\an1}Hey, Harvey, the diner
named a sandwich after me.

13:31.377 --> 13:34.046
- Oh, my gosh.
That's amazing.

13:34.113 --> 13:37.383
{\an3}You'll go down in history.
Like Rudolph.

13:37.449 --> 13:38.651
- I don't know who that is,

13:38.717 --> 13:40.319
{\an1}so that's not really
a good example.

13:40.386 --> 13:44.190
- Forget Mr. Fruit Bowl.
Give me a bite of that bad boy.

13:44.256 --> 13:47.526
- Oh, Harvey, you are saying
all the right words now.

13:47.593 --> 13:50.696
- [chewing]
- So, what do you think?

13:50.763 --> 13:52.431
{\an1}Come on.
Don't keep me waiting.

13:52.498 --> 13:55.834
{\an3}- Not too salty,
not too sweet.

13:55.901 --> 13:57.703
{\an3}Doesn't really
taste like anything.

13:57.770 --> 13:59.004
I like it!

13:59.071 --> 14:01.073
- Oh, this is great.
I knew you'd like it.

14:01.140 --> 14:02.808
{\an1}See this,
this is why we're so close.

14:02.875 --> 14:04.677
- Hey, what's up?
Ooh, what's that?

14:04.743 --> 14:07.413
- None of your ding-dang
business is what it is.

14:07.479 --> 14:09.114
But if you must know,

14:09.181 --> 14:10.883
{\an1}the diner named
this sandwich after me

14:10.950 --> 14:12.785
because I'm just so unique.

14:12.851 --> 14:15.054
- Oh, sweet.
You can order off the menu here?

14:15.120 --> 14:16.755
Hey, old guy, I'm ready.

14:16.822 --> 14:20.292
- Here comes the lightning feet.

14:22.127 --> 14:25.164
Here I come.
- I want a hoagie

14:25.231 --> 14:28.167
with a slice of pizza
stuffed in the middle,

14:28.234 --> 14:32.438
and drizzle the whole thing
in, uh, chocolate fudge.

14:32.504 --> 14:35.975
{\an1}- What is that, like, a sandwich
for a confused person?

14:36.041 --> 14:39.144
Ha, I don't--
- What a special order.

14:39.211 --> 14:41.914
- What?
- I think I'll add that

14:41.981 --> 14:45.184
to the menu.
What's your name?

14:45.251 --> 14:46.318
- Wade!

14:46.385 --> 14:49.021
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:49.088 --> 14:50.556
- [gasps]
[bell dings]

14:50.623 --> 14:52.157
- Order up.

14:52.224 --> 14:53.726
{\an3}- See?
That wasn't so hard.

14:53.792 --> 14:55.194
{\an3}That took, like, what?
Five seconds?

14:55.261 --> 14:58.697
{\an1}- Wh--wh--why would anyone
want your disgusting sandwich

14:58.764 --> 15:01.300
when they could have
a classic like mine?

15:01.367 --> 15:02.301
- I don't know.

15:02.368 --> 15:03.602
{\an3}It does look
kind of interesting.

15:03.669 --> 15:06.171
- Yeah, that looks pretty good.
- Who are you?

15:06.238 --> 15:07.740
Get outta here!

15:07.806 --> 15:11.777
Ugh, how can I be special
when dumb Wade has a sandwich?

15:11.844 --> 15:14.213
I gotta prove mine's better.

15:15.881 --> 15:17.616
[gasps]
I know!

15:17.683 --> 15:19.818
- Ready for round seven, Jeremy?

15:19.885 --> 15:22.154
You've been here all day.

15:22.221 --> 15:23.589
- [slurping]

15:23.656 --> 15:25.924
Oh, yeah.
Uh, speaking of...

15:25.991 --> 15:27.826
uh, can I get the bathroom key?

15:27.893 --> 15:29.995
- Here you go.
- Oh, boy, gotta go.

15:30.062 --> 15:31.930
- Hey, stop right there, Jeremy.

15:31.997 --> 15:33.432
I have an emergency.

15:33.499 --> 15:34.967
- Oh, oh, can it wait?

15:35.034 --> 15:38.404
{\an3}- Jeremy, I am not letting you
leave this booth.

15:38.470 --> 15:39.505
{\an1}- Go on.

15:39.571 --> 15:42.041
{\an3}- Okay, well,
as a fellow snacker,

15:42.107 --> 15:45.110
{\an3}I am an avid viewer of
your online snack review series.

15:45.177 --> 15:47.646
- Oh, you've seen those videos?

15:47.713 --> 15:49.515
<i>Uh, hello, everyone.</i>

15:49.581 --> 15:53.085
This is the new line of
pizza-flavored toaster treats,

15:53.152 --> 15:55.654
and, uh, I'm gonna eat 'em.

15:55.721 --> 15:57.656
Okay, here I go.

15:57.723 --> 15:59.992
[gnawing]
<i>[static]</i>

16:00.059 --> 16:02.194
[gnawing]
Oh, these are really good.

16:02.261 --> 16:04.330
Oh, these are even better.

16:06.065 --> 16:08.801
<i>[lilting upbeat music]</i>

16:08.867 --> 16:11.337
So, yeah,

16:11.403 --> 16:14.907
that concludes
"Snacking With Jeremy."

16:14.973 --> 16:18.977
Oof, I'm gonna go sleep
at the hospital now.

16:19.044 --> 16:21.213
Until next time.

16:21.280 --> 16:23.782
- So, anyway,
I have two sandwiches here:

16:23.849 --> 16:26.418
one that's delicious
and one that's disgusting,

16:26.485 --> 16:29.955
and I was kinda hoping that you,
as a man of taste,

16:30.022 --> 16:32.424
can convince the people
that my sandwich is better.

16:32.491 --> 16:35.227
Basically, I want to use you.
[camera beeps]

16:35.294 --> 16:37.162
Boy, it sounds kind of bad
when I say it like that.

16:37.229 --> 16:38.630
[camera beeps]
Hey!

16:38.697 --> 16:39.965
Oh, what the heck?

16:40.032 --> 16:41.400
You--you already ate 'em?

16:41.467 --> 16:42.835
- Oh, oops.

16:42.901 --> 16:45.237
{\an3}- Well, can you at least tell me
which one was better?

16:45.304 --> 16:47.506
- There were two sandwiches?

16:47.573 --> 16:49.041
- [groans]

16:49.108 --> 16:51.944
<i>[ambient music]</i>

16:52.010 --> 16:54.480
No one can resist a free sample.

16:54.546 --> 16:56.448
All right, come and get--

16:56.515 --> 16:57.616
oh.

16:57.683 --> 17:00.152
[wind blowing]

17:01.153 --> 17:03.322
{\an1}Cards are boring.
Come with me.

17:03.389 --> 17:05.624
Don't pretend like
there's somewhere you gotta be.

17:05.691 --> 17:07.925
- Come on.
Live, darn you!

17:07.992 --> 17:09.027
- Oh, my gosh!

17:09.094 --> 17:10.662
You gotta try this sandwich.

17:10.729 --> 17:13.031
{\an3}Come on.
He'll be fine.

17:13.098 --> 17:16.167
[clears throat]
So I'm sure you're all wondering

17:16.234 --> 17:19.204
why I brought you here today.
- Um--

17:19.271 --> 17:21.272
- No, no, no, I'm not actually
taking questions.

17:21.339 --> 17:23.942
All right, so you can
stop holding your applause

17:24.009 --> 17:25.877
because here it is.

17:25.944 --> 17:28.280
The Dade.
Ain't she a beaut?

17:28.347 --> 17:30.149
{\an3}Get 'em while they're
nice and hot.

17:30.215 --> 17:32.885
{\an1}Or, uh, room temperature,
I guess.

17:32.951 --> 17:35.354
So, in closing,
be sure to tell your friends

17:35.421 --> 17:38.490
all about The Dade
and about me, Dade.

17:38.557 --> 17:40.192
You know,
not to brag or anything,

17:40.259 --> 17:43.228
but the diner kind of
named the sandwich after me

17:43.295 --> 17:45.697
because I am so special.
- Wait.

17:45.764 --> 17:48.367
You can get a sandwich named
after yourself at the diner?

17:48.434 --> 17:51.103
- Well, technically,
anyone can get a sandwich, but--

17:51.170 --> 17:52.638
wait, wait, wait!

17:52.704 --> 17:54.339
[indistinct chatter]

17:54.406 --> 17:57.075
No!

17:57.142 --> 17:58.977
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

17:59.044 --> 18:00.212
- I want one.
- Me next!

18:00.279 --> 18:01.213
- I was here first.
- I want one!

18:01.280 --> 18:03.649
- Lots of business today.

18:03.715 --> 18:05.417
- I want
a single piece of cheese

18:05.484 --> 18:07.920
wrapped in lettuce.
Bib lettuce if you have it,

18:07.986 --> 18:09.354
but you probably don't have it.

18:09.421 --> 18:11.957
- No, that order's not special!

18:12.024 --> 18:13.258
- Can I get a piece of bread?

18:13.325 --> 18:14.626
But can you burn it a little?

18:14.693 --> 18:17.162
{\an1}- That's toast!
You just ordered toast!

18:17.229 --> 18:21.066
- What a special order.
- No!

18:21.133 --> 18:23.836
- I think I'll add that
to the menu.

18:23.902 --> 18:26.839
What's your na--

18:26.905 --> 18:29.508
Oh, dear.

18:29.575 --> 18:32.911
Looks like we're outta room.
- Oh, phew.

18:32.978 --> 18:37.049
- Well, let's just take off
some of these stinkers.

18:37.115 --> 18:40.052
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:40.118 --> 18:47.259
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:48.293 --> 18:49.928
[video game buzzing]
- Huh?

18:49.995 --> 18:51.597
Oh, yeah, that's cool.

18:51.663 --> 18:53.565
- All right, who's next?

18:53.632 --> 18:55.434
all: Me!

18:55.501 --> 18:58.003
- This--this doesn't
make any sense.

18:58.070 --> 19:00.405
[sputters]

19:00.472 --> 19:02.608
This can't be happening.
[hyperventilates]

19:02.674 --> 19:05.677
This must be some kind
of horrible nightmare.

19:05.744 --> 19:07.713
[grunts]

19:07.779 --> 19:09.681
Ugh!

19:09.748 --> 19:11.250
They--they rejected me.

19:11.316 --> 19:12.951
[hyperventilating]

19:13.018 --> 19:15.220
They all rejected me!

19:15.287 --> 19:17.789
I've been cast aside
like a common rag.

19:17.856 --> 19:19.591
- [whistling]

19:19.658 --> 19:20.893
- Hey!
- Huh?

19:20.959 --> 19:22.227
- Tell me why.

19:22.294 --> 19:23.762
Why don't they want me?

19:23.829 --> 19:26.265
- Uh, I don't know.
Um, you're clingy?

19:26.331 --> 19:29.134
{\an3}You come on too strong?
Leave me alone, man.

19:29.201 --> 19:31.770
I just wanted a milkshake!

19:31.837 --> 19:34.773
- [laughs demonically]

19:34.840 --> 19:37.709
- [gasps]
The diner.

19:37.776 --> 19:38.944
[growls]

19:39.011 --> 19:41.213
Oh, you don't think I'm special.

19:41.280 --> 19:44.750
Well, I'll show you
who's special.

19:44.816 --> 19:46.218
<i>[eerie music]</i>

19:46.285 --> 19:49.254
I'm gonna get revenge
on that horrible diner

19:49.321 --> 19:51.990
and everyone in it.
- [snoring]

19:52.057 --> 19:55.227
- Time to set the bait.

19:55.294 --> 19:56.795
Wake up, little buddy.

19:56.862 --> 19:58.730
{\an3}- [murmurs]

20:00.332 --> 20:03.769
- Who wants a sandwich?

20:03.835 --> 20:05.871
Well, come and get it.

20:05.938 --> 20:07.306
[stomach growls]

20:07.372 --> 20:09.207
You know you want it!

20:09.274 --> 20:11.176
Dinner is served.

20:11.243 --> 20:13.745
[laughs crazily]

20:13.812 --> 20:16.481
- [growls]

20:16.548 --> 20:19.685
- [growling]
- [laughing crazily]

20:27.359 --> 20:29.795
It's working.
I can see the diner.

20:29.861 --> 20:30.896
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:30.963 --> 20:32.831
There it is.
Destroy it.

20:32.898 --> 20:34.866
I command you to eat the diner.

20:34.933 --> 20:38.070
Eat it!
[laughs crazily]

20:39.504 --> 20:41.506
Oh, no, I really didn't
think this thing through.

20:41.573 --> 20:43.575
[screaming]
Oh, great.

20:43.642 --> 20:45.277
Now somebody wants
the stupid--

20:47.813 --> 20:50.449
[stomach rumbling]

20:50.515 --> 20:51.717
- [burps]

20:51.783 --> 20:54.720
[gagging]

20:56.722 --> 20:58.090
- [groans]

20:58.156 --> 21:00.125
Oh, I'm alive.

21:00.192 --> 21:01.860
Ah, hey, what gives?

21:01.927 --> 21:03.261
Didn't I taste good?

21:03.328 --> 21:05.731
- Mm...
[grumbles]

21:05.797 --> 21:08.567
A little too bland.

21:08.634 --> 21:10.936
- Oh, everybody's a critic.

21:11.003 --> 21:12.204
Dang foodies.

21:12.270 --> 21:16.174
Well, I guess nobody wants
The Dade.

21:16.241 --> 21:18.210
Or me.

21:18.276 --> 21:19.811
[both snoring]

21:19.878 --> 21:22.814
<i>[soft music]</i>

21:22.881 --> 21:25.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:25.484 --> 21:27.085
All right, you win.

21:27.152 --> 21:28.253
- Hey, where were you?

21:28.320 --> 21:29.955
{\an1}[sniffs]
You smell weird.

21:30.022 --> 21:31.256
- [sighs]

21:31.323 --> 21:32.991
[bell dings]
- Order up.

21:33.058 --> 21:34.860
One Dade.

21:34.926 --> 21:38.296
- [gasps]
Wade, you ordered my sandwich.

21:38.363 --> 21:40.766
- Turns out hot fudge
and pizza's only rad,

21:40.832 --> 21:42.167
like, the first two times.

21:42.234 --> 21:44.703
I decided to go for a classic.

21:44.770 --> 21:47.773
- Oh, man, it feels good
to hear someone say that.

21:47.839 --> 21:50.809
- Yeah, sometimes I find
it's the old reliable stuff

21:50.876 --> 21:52.010
that I like best.

21:52.077 --> 21:54.112
You know what I mean?

21:54.179 --> 21:56.915
<i>[quirky upbeat music]</i>

21:56.982 --> 21:59.718
- Can you, uh--can you
repeat that for the camera?

22:01.853 --> 22:04.790
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.856 --> 22:11.797
{\an1}<i>♪ ♪</i>
